card_id_1.desc: There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

card_id_2.desc: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

card_id_3.desc: The flower on its back catches the sun's rays. The sunlight is then absorbed and used for energy.

card_id_4.desc: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

card_id_5.desc: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.

card_id_6.desc: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.

card_id_7.desc: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

card_id_8.desc: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

card_id_9.desc: Shoots water at prey while in the water. Withdraws into its shell when in danger.

card_id_10.desc: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

card_id_11.desc: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can't withstand a harsh attack.

card_id_12.desc: In battle, it flaps its wings at great speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

card_id_13.desc: Often found in forests and grasslands. It has a sharp, toxic barb of around two inches on top of its head.

card_id_14.desc: This Pokémon is in a temporary stage while making its body. It is almost completely unable to move on its own.

card_id_15.desc: Extremely territorial. No one should ever approach its nest—this is for their own safety.

card_id_17.desc: This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

card_id_18.desc: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.

card_id_19.desc: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

card_id_20.desc: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.

card_id_21.desc: Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

card_id_22.desc: A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

card_id_42.desc: Uses its alluring eyes to enrapture its foe. It then sings a pleasing melody that lulls the foe to sleep.

card_id_43.desc: Adores round objects. It wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

card_id_44.desc: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily Pokémon will use psychokinetic powers.

card_id_45.desc: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

card_id_46.desc: The swirl on its belly is its insides showing through the skin. It looks clearer after it eats.

card_id_47.desc: Using its psychic power, it generates a rippling field of anti-gravity that floats its Trainer in midair.

card_id_48.desc: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

card_id_49.desc: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

card_id_57.desc: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.

card_id_62.desc: Koffing emits toxic gases from the poisonous substances it ingests. The skull and crossbones pattern on its body serves as a warning to stay away.

card_id_60.desc: This Pokémon is known as the Dragon Pokémon. It is very kind and can fly extremely long distances.

card_id_63.desc: Steelix is a massive, serpentine Pokémon made of steel. Its body is impervious to most attacks, and it can burrow through the ground at incredible speeds.

card_id_65.desc: Gastly is almost invisible, a gaseous Pokémon that cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.

card_id_67.desc: Diglett are known for their burrowing skills. They can dig through the ground at a speed of 60 mph, making tunnels that are perfect for hiding.

card_id_68.desc: Pidgey is a common sight in grassy areas. It flies around in search of small insects to bring back to its nest.

card_id_69.desc: Pikachu is an Electric-type Pokémon known for its small size and lightning-fast moves. It stores electricity in its cheek pouches.

card_id_72.desc: Articuno is a legendary Ice/Flying-type Pokémon. It is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains, bringing a chill to the air.

card_id_73.desc: Tyranitar is a powerful Rock/Dark-type Pokémon. Its appearance alone can strike fear into the hearts of those who encounter it in the wild.

card_id_77.desc: Mewtwo is a legendary Psychic-type Pokémon. Created through genetic manipulation, it is highly intelligent and possesses immense psychic power.

card_id_78.desc: Mew is a mythical Psychic-type Pokémon. It is said to possess the genetic code of all Pokémon and is believed to have the ability to learn any move.
